        "text": "Save Orchard Hill speakers set \nCEDAR FALLS — A Lenten Lunch speaker series is planned at Orchard Hill Church, 3900 Orchard Hill Drive, each Wednesday through March 21. \nThe meal will be served from 11:30 a.m. to 12:10 p.m., with a speaker program from 12:15 to 12:45 p.m. \nEveryone is welcome. A meal of soup, bread and dessert will be provided ($4 donation suggested). \nThe speaker schedule includes: Wednesday — Paul Sabino, Candeo, Church. Feb. 21 — Quovadis Martin, Hope City Church, Waterloo. Feb. 28 — Tim Boettger, Western Home Communities. Pancake day slated Tuesday \nCEDAR FALLS — Our Redeemer Lutheran Church, 904 Bluff St., will host the annual Shrove Tuesday pancake day Feb. 13. \nLunch will be served from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m., and dinner will be served from 5 to 7 p.m. It includes all-you-can-eat pancakes plus sausage and applesauce. \nTickets, available at the door, are $6 for 10 years of age through adults and free for ages 9 years and younger. Church to host Sunday dinner \nWATERLOO — The Mission Department of Mount Carmel will host a “Birthday Bash” dinner Sunday following morning worship. \nThis is a “dine-in” only dinner — no carry outs or deliveries. Call the church at 233-9482 for further information. VFW announces coming events \nWATERLOO — The Sullivan Brothers VFW is now holding jam sessions Saturdays. \nThe first will feature a group of musicians from the University of Northern Iowa from 3 to 6 p.m. Saturday. \nEveryone is welcome to listen, and there is no admission charge. \nDonations for the musicians will be appreciated. Game night and potluck also are set to start at 4 p.m. at the post. \nOther VFW activities include crockpot meals from 5 to 7 p.m. Tuesdays, bingo from 5 to 7 p.m. Thursdays, karaoke from 8 to 1 a.m. Fridays, a pepper tournament and snacks from 2 to 4 p.m. followed by pool league at 7 p.m. Sundays. \nThe Sullivan Brothers VFW Post is open to the public at 1406 Commercial St. Country music jam scheduled \nCEDAR FALLS — The Country Good Timers will host a country music jam session from 1 to 4:30 p.m. Sunday at the Cedar Falls Community Center on Main Street. \nThere will be a Valentine theme, and people are welcome to wear red. Independence blood drive set \nINDEPENDENCE — There will be a Buchanan County community blood drive from noon to 5:30 p.m. Tuesday at BCHC Wellness Center, 1600 First St. East. \nFor an appointment, go to lifeservebloodcenter.org or call (800) 287-4903. Love",
