        "text": "\nEvents \nFriday, Feb. 9 \nBLOOD DRIVE: 10 a.m. to 3 p.m., Lower Cape Library, 2600 Bayshore Road, Villas . 609-463-6386 or RedCrossBlood.org . \nBLOOD DRIVE: 2 to 7 p.m.; walk-ins welcome, but appointments preferred; Hamilton Mall, 4403 Black Horse Pike, Mays Landing . 609-382-4728 or RedCrossBlood.org . \nJAZZ DANCE FOR ADULTS: 1 to 2 p.m.; taught by Susan Pennypacker; warm-up/workout coupled with modern jazz technique; Public Library, 6300 Atlantic Ave., Wildwood Crest , registration required. 609-463-6386 or CMCLibrary.org . \nSaturday, Feb. 10 \nCLASSIC MOVIE: 2 to 4 p.m.; for all ages; Atlantic County Library, 40 Farragut Ave., Mays Landing , free. 609-625-2776 or AtlanticLibrary.org . \nCOMEDY NIGHT: 8 to 11 p.m.; hosted by the Wildwood Catholic Crusader Club; food, drinks for purchase; Harbor Square Theater, 271 96th St., Stone Harbor , $20 advance, $25 at the door. 609-374-1274. \nDELIGHTFUL DATE DAYS: 11 a.m. to 3:30 p.m. Feb. 10, 11; two-for-one tower climb; Absecon Lighthouse, 31 S. Rhode Island Ave., Atlantic City , $7. 609-449-1360 or AbseconLighthouse.org . \nVALENTINE’S DINNER AND COMEDY SHOW: 5 to 10 p.m.; with comedians Davin, Sean Morton and Natty Bumpercar; Mystic Island American Legion Post 493, 420 Radio Road, Little Egg Harbor Township , $10 dinner, $20 show or $25 combo. 609-296-9771 or GingerNinjaComedy.com . \nVALENTINE’S DINNER AND LIVE SHOW: 4 to 11 p.m.; Gentleman Jim with a tribute to Elvis and rock and roll; Galloway Township Elks Lodge 2845, 120 S. New York Road, Galloway Township , $30, advance reservations required. 609-412-1657 or GallowayElks.com . \nSunday, Feb. 11 \nPRE-PROM FASHION SHOW: 4 to 8 p.m.; Holy Spirit High School, 500 S. New Road, Absecon , $5 advance, $8 at the door. HolySpiritHighSchool.com . \nDining out \nFriday, Feb. 9 \nBAKED CHICKEN DINNER: 5 to 8 p.m.; VFW Post 6257, 556 Woodbine Ave., Belleplain , $10. 609-861-2298. \nTuesday, Feb. 13 \nVALENTINE’S DINNER: 6:30 to 8:30 p.m. Feb. 13, 14; Academy of Culinary Arts students prepare and present five-course gourmet vegetarian meal; Careme’s Gourmet Restaurant, 5100 E. Black Horse Pike, Mays Landing , $36 adults, $26 students/low income. 856-694-2887 or AmericanVegan.org . \nFundraisers \nFriday, Feb. 9 \n‘LITTLE LOVE, LOTTA LAUGHS’: 8 to 10 p.m.; comedy night to support the Atlantic City Arts Foundation; headliner LaTice Klapa and an open mic contest; Little Water Distillery, 807 Baltic Avenue, Unit B, Atlantic City, $25. AtlanticCityArtsFoundation.org . \nSunday, Feb. 11 \nJAZZ, FOOD & WINE EVENT: 3 to 6 p.m.; annual scholarship fundraiser for Atlantic City Alumnae Chapter, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority Inc.; Renault Winery Resort, 72 N. Bremen Ave., Egg Harbor City , $60. . \nWINE & CHEESE FUNDRAISER: 1 to 3 p.m.; hosted by Liberty and Prosperity; keynote speaker retired Superior Court Judge Paul Porreca of Cumberland County; Irish Pub, 164 Saint James Place, Atlantic City , $75 for one ticket, $100 for two. 609-927-7333 or LibertyAndProsperity.com . \nFor kids \nSaturday, Feb. 10 \nBASKETBALL FREE THROW CONTEST: 10 a.m. to noon; hosted by Knights of Columbus Council 3451; open to ages 9 to 14; age verification required; winners advance to district, regional and state championships; Saint Vincent De Paul Regional School, 5809 Main St., Mays Landing . 609-338-3961. \n‘BETCHA CAN’T EAT JUST ONE’: 3 to 4 p.m.; for kids and teens; taste test to honor African-American inventor of the potato chip; Free Public Library, 1 N. Tennessee Ave., Atlantic City , free. 609-345-2269 or ACFPL.org . \nLEGO CLUB: 10:30 to 11:30 a.m. every other Saturday through March 24; for all ages; Atlantic County Library, 1 Swift Ave., Egg Harbor Township . 609-927-8664 or AtlanticLibrary.org . \nLEGO CLUB: 2 to 3 p.m. Saturdays through Feb. 24; for ages 6 to 12; Free Public Library, 1 N. Tennessee Ave., Atlantic City , free. 609-345-2269 or ACFPL.org . \nSECOND SATURDAY CRAFTERNOONS: 2:30 to 3:30 p.m.; for ages 8 to 14; arts, crafts and cool stuff; Atlantic County Library, 306 E. Jimmie Leeds Road, Galloway Township , registration required. 609-652-2352 or AtlanticLibrary.org . \nVALENTINE CRAFT: 11 a.m. to noon; for ages 6 to 12; Atlantic County Library, 1 Swift Ave., Egg Harbor Township , registration required. 609-927-8664 or AtlanticLibrary.org . \nVALENTINE HEART CARD HOLDER: 10:30 to 11:15 a.m.; for ages 3 to 12; Atlantic County Library, 201 S. 15th St., Brigantine . 609-266-0110. \nGroups \nFriday, Feb. 9 \nNARCOTICS ANONYMOUS: 7 to 8 p.m. Feb. 9, 16, 23, Conference Rooms 3 & 4, Cape Regional Medical Center, Cape May Court House . 609-463-4043 or CapeRegional.com . \nSaturday, Feb. 10 \nSTAY FOCUSED PHOTO CLUB: 9:30 a.m. second Saturdays; for photographers of all ages and skill levels; Stockton University, Room F-111, Jimmie Leeds Road, Galloway Township . StayFocusedPhoto.club. \nHealth, fitness \nFriday, Feb. 9 \nSENIORS FITNESS AND DANCE: 3 to 4 p.m. second Fridays; Public Library, 9516 Second Ave., Stone Harbor . 609-463-6386 or CMCLibrary.org . \nTAI CHI AND QI GONG: 10:30 to 11:30 a.m. Fridays through Feb. 23; for ages 18 and older; Free Public Library, 1 N. Tennessee Ave., Atlantic City , free. 609-345-2269 or ACFPL.org . \nSaturday, Feb. 10 \nMINDFULNESS MEDITATION: 11 a.m. to noon; for adults; Atlantic County Library, 40 Farragut Ave., Mays Landing , registration requested. 609-625-2776 or AtlanticLibrary.org . \nYOGA FOR BEGINNERS: 9:30 to 10:30 a.m. Saturdays, Public Library, 30 West Mechanic St., Cape May Court House . 609-463-6386 or CMCLibrary.org . \nZUMBA GOLD FOR THE ACTIVE OLDER ADULT: 10 to 11 a.m. Saturdays; Public Library, 9516 Second Ave., Stone Harbor . 609-463-6386 or CMCLibrary.org . \nMonday, Feb. 12 \nCHAIR YOGA: 3:30 to 4:30 p.m. Mondays; gentle form of yoga that is practiced sitting on a chair, or standing using a chair for support; Public Library, 9516 Second Ave., Stone Harbor . 609-463-6386 or CMCLibrary.org . \nESSENTIAL OILS PRESENTATION: 6 to 8 p.m.; “Using Essential Oils with Your Physical and Mental Mind/Body Practice,” presented by Debbie Valletto, Wellness Advocate; Public Library, 30 W. Mechanic St., Cape May Court House . 609-463-6386 or CMCLibrary.org . \nFREE DIABETES SELF-MANAGEMENT WORKSHOP SERIES: 10 a.m. to noon; six-week workshop series; Millville Sharing Center, 130 S. Second St., Millville , free. 856-825-8779 or QualityInsights-QIN.org . \nNAMI SUPPORT MEETINGS: 7 to 9 p.m. second Monday of the month; hosted by the National Alliance on Mental Illness; open to the public; supportive and stigma free discussion group for family members of those with mental illness and those who need mental health support; Absecon United Methodist Church, 100 Pitney Road, Absecon , free. 609-927-0215 or NAMI.org . \nYOGA WITH CECI: 10:30 to 11:30 a.m.; Monday Morning Yoga at the Library; Cumberland County Library, 800 E. Commerce St., Bridgeton , donations accepted. 856-453-2210 or CCLNJ.org . \nZUMBA GOLD FOR THE ACTIVE OLDER ADULT: 10 to 11 a.m. Mondays; taught by Cathy Cashmere, licensed Zumba and Zumba Gold instructor; Public Library, 4800 Central Ave., Sea Isle City . 609-463-6386 or CMCLibrary.org . \nTuesday, Feb. 13 \nAL-ANON FAMILY GROUP: 8 to 9 p.m. Tuesdays; support group for people whose loved ones suffer from alcoholism; St. John Lutheran Church, 1001 Central Ave., Ocean City . 609-399-0717. \nALZHEIMER’S SUPPORT GROUP: 5:15 to 8 p.m., second Tuesdays; for family members and caregivers of people with Alzheimer’s or Dementia; learn about resources, find strategies for dealing with a loved one with memory loss, and meet others in similar circumstances; meetings are lead by Jamie Rudy, CDP, CSW; Seashore Gardens Living Center, 22 W. Jimmie Leeds Road, Galloway Township , free. 609-404-4848. \nGROUP REIKI HEALING: 1 to 2:15 p.m. Tuesdays through Feb. 27; Enlightened Cafe, 6414 Ventnor Ave., Ventnor City , $15. HansenFoundationNJ.org . \nPILATES YOGA FUSION: 10 to 11 a.m. Tuesdays; taught by Kathleen Jespersen; Lower Cape Library, 2600 Bayshore Road, Villas . 609-463-6386 or CMCLibrary.org . \nYOGA FOR BEGINNERS: 3 p.m. Tuesdays; taught by Tammy Decker; Public Library, 9516 Second Ave., Stone Harbor . 609-463-6386 or CMCLibrary.org . \nYOGA PILATES FUSION: 10 to 11 a.m. Tuesdays; pilates-yoga fusion exercises teach students how to use core stability for every-day movement; Lower Cape Library, 2600 Bayshore Road, Villas . 609-463-6386 or CMCLibrary.org . \nZUMBA FITNESS AT COURT HOUSE LIBRARY: 4:30 to 5:30 p.m. Tuesdays; Latin dance-inspired fitness class; Public Library, 30 W. Mechanic St., Cape May Court House . 609-463-6386 or CMCLibrary.org . \nZUMBA FITNESS AT WILDWOOD CREST LIBRARY: 9:30 to 10:30 a.m. Tuesdays; Latin dance-inspired fitness class; Public Library, 6300 Atlantic Ave., Wildwood Crest . 609-463-6386 or CMCLibrary.org . \nWednesday, Feb. 14 \nYOGA WITH CECI: 6:30 to 7:30 p.m.; Wednesday Evening Yoga; Cumberland County Library, 800 E. Commerce St., Bridgeton , donations accepted. 856-453-2210 or CCLNJ.org . \nMusic \nFriday, Feb. 9 \n‘MUSIC PRESENTATION OF VOICE AND PIANO’: 6:30 to 8:30 p.m., Public Library, 2305 Atlantic Ave., Longport . 609-487-7403 or LongportNJ.Gov/Library . \nSaturday, Feb. 10 \nLIVE DIXIELAND JAZZ: 8:30 to 11:30 p.m.; performance by the A.C. New Orleans Jazz Band; part of Gregory’s Cajun festival; presented by the South Jersey Jazz Society; Gregory’s Restaurant & Bar, 900 Shore Road, Somers Point . 609-927-6665 or GregorysBar.com . \nMonday, Feb. 12 \nSINGING AMBASSADORS REHEARSALS: 7 to 8:30 p.m. Mondays through March 12; open to all singers ages 14 and older; Fiorelli Senior Center, 6th and Elmer streets, Vineland . 856-563-0376 or 856-692-6420. \nReligion \n{strong style=”font-size: 1.5em;”}Sunday, Feb. 11{/strong} \nBOY SCOUT SUNDAY: 10:30 to 11:30 a.m.; honors local scouts; South Vineland United Methodist Church, corner of Main Road and Sherman Avenue, Vineland . 856-692-2152. \nFAMILY & FRIENDS DAY: 4 p.m., guest preacher the Rev. James Coaxum III of St. James AME Atlantic City; New Bethel AME Church, 414 N. Seventh St., Vineland . 856-691-1349. \nTuesday, Feb. 13 \nADULT BIBLE STUDY: 7 to 9 p.m. Tuesdays through June 2018; Holy Trinity Greek Orthodox Church, 7004 Ridge Ave., Egg Harbor Township . 609-653-8092 or HolyTrinityEggHarbor.com . \nMonday, Feb. 17 \nBLACK HISTORY MONTH SERVICE: 7 p.m., hosted by Pastors United for Community Service; guest speakers; all welcome; Macedonia Baptist Church, Pittsburgh Avenue and Old Mays Landing Road, Egg Harbor City . 609-965-4211. \nSunday, Feb. 25 \nANNUAL FELLOWSHIP SERVICE: 3:30 p.m., with the congregation of St. John AME Zion Church in Mizpah; all welcome; New Bethel AME Church, 414 N. Seventh St., Vineland . 856-691-1349. \nWednesday, March 7 \nMONTH OF CULTURE AT BETH ISRAEL: March 7: bus trip to the Metropolitan Opera in New York to see La Boheme, 2 p.m. departure from Beth Israel, 2501 Shore Road, Northfield , $95, 609-432-2983; 7 p.m. March 12: The Keshet Chaim Dance Ensemble, Milton & Betty Katz JCC, 501 N. Jerome Ave., Margate , $18 advance, $25 at the door, free ages 18 and younger; 7:30 p.m. March 17: vodka and spirits from the Little Water Distillery and live Klezmer/Blue Grass music by the Klezmer Mountain Boys, Beth Israel, Northfield ; $36. 609-641-3600 or BethIsraelNorthfield.org . \nReunions \nATLANTIC CITY HIGH SCHOOL CLASS OF 1971: 8 p.m. Aug. 18; 65th birthday celebration for all members of Class of 1971; Smithville Inn, Galloway Township; $45. Call David Goodelman at 609-674-8873 or email . \nTrips \nTRIP TO METROPOLITAN OPERA: 2 to 11:30 p.m. March 7; Franco Zefferelli’s classic production of La Boheme at the Metropolitan Opera in New York City; 2 p.m. departure from Beth Israel Reform Congregation, 2501 Shore Road, Northfield; $95, reservations due by Jan. 5 . 609-432-2983 or . \nPHILADELPHIA FLOWER SHOW: March 8; hosted by Partners in Preservation; 8 a.m. departure from Wildwood bus terminal parking lot; 9:30 a.m. flower show, 2 p.m. Shen Yun show at Merrian Theatre, Philadelphia, PA; $140. 609-214-2253 or 609-729-4515. \nRESORTS CASINO BUS TRIP: 10:15 a.m. to 6 p.m. March 19; continues on third Mondays; hosted by the Manahawkin Senior Social Club; departs from Moose Lodge parking lot, 120 Route 72 West, Stafford Township, $28. 609-597-5222 or 609-607-9970. ",
