        "title": "Leaders Credit Union wins blood donation competition",
        "text": "Leaders Credit Union wins blood donation competition February 8, 2018 WBBJ 7 Eyewitness News Staff , \nJACKSON, Tenn.–Local banks competed to see who can roll up their sleeves and bring in the most blood donations. This is the second year Leaders Credit Union won the competition, bringing in 57 blood donations. Bancorp South, First Tennessee Bank, Simmons Bank, Regions Bank and First Bank were involved in the friendly competition. In total, 176 people donated blood. \n“This is extremely important for those patients that are in need here in our own hospitals, but also are suffering needing transfusions in our cancer centers,” said John Miller, CEO of Life Line Blood Services. \nThe blood is donated to cancer patients, elderly and sick patients.",
