        "title": "Greater Derry Diaper Drive set",
        "text": "Greater Derry Diaper Drive set Feb 8, 2018 \n\nDERRY — The fifth annual Diaper Drive to support The Upper Room's Teen Parenting for Parenting Success, or TIPS, program. Collection sites are at RE/MAX Innovative, 66 Gilcreast Road, Londonderry; The Grind Rail Trail Cafe, 5 West Broadway, Derry; Carina's Cakes on Crystal Avenue, Derry; and East Derry Tire and Auto Inc., 46 East Derry Road, Derry. Local realtor Susan Ochoa is sponsoring the drive and collections are held through March 3. \nTimberlane Regional School District Health and Wellness Fair \nPLAISTOW — The Timberlane Regional School District Wellness Committee will hold its 9th annual Health and Wellness Fair on March 13 from 2:30 to 5:30 p.m.. The free health fair will take place at the Timberlane Regional High School cafeteria and gymnasium . \nThere will be information on nutrition, diabetes awareness, concussion awareness, disease, colon cancer, blood pressure screenings, hearing screenings, acupuncture, naturopathic medicine, massage, health and fitness topics, and many more informative booths. \nAlso, the marrow registry, “Be the Match and Donate Life” organizations will be at the health fair. For those interested, it involves a simple cheek swab and is covered by most health insurances (please bring your health card). Michael’s Fund of Fall River, MA will cover the cost for those without coverage. You never know who in the Greater Timberlane Community we may be able to help. \n\nThe American Red Cross will also be having a blood drive. \nHannah Dustin Quilters Guild annual quilt show \nHUDSON — The Hannah Dustin Quilters Guild 29th annual quilt show will take place on Friday, April 27 from noon to 7 p.m. and Saturday, April 28 from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. at the Hudson Community Center in Hudson. \nEvery spring, the guild hosts a quilt show that includes quilts of all sizes and designs. Also included are vendors, refreshments, raffle baskets, a boutique, and pre-made quilt blocks to get you started to make your own quilt. A quilt made by guild members will be raffled near the end of the show on Saturday. \n\nGeneral Admission is $8 and free for children under 12 years old. \n\nMack's to serve up pie contest \n\nLONDONDERRY — Mack's Apples will be hosting its pie contest on Saturday, Feb. 17 at the farm stand on Mammoth Road. Pie entries will be judged by a panel of judges and awards will be given to those taking top tasting honors in various categories. \nClothing ministry opens \n\nDERRY — Renew opens Saturday, Feb. 10, 8 to 10:30 a.m. at Calvary Bible Church, 145 Hampstead Road. The clothing ministry now offers winter clothing and is open to families on a budget or anyone in need and Derry residency is not required. Renew gives away free, gently used apparel donated by the community. Enter at marquee sign at Calvary Bible Church. Donations of good condition, modern clothing can be placed in donation bin by the door at any time. No housewares, toys, books or bedding. Call for information at 434-1516, visit Renew on Facebook or email to . Tags",
