        "text": "Moore Insurance Agency Leads Charity Initiative to Raise Donations for Blood Cancer Research Share Article A Houston area insurance provider is announcing a charity drive to raise awareness and donations for research into blood cancer cures and treatments We’re excited about the upcoming Leukemia & Lymphoma Society event, and our agency is committed to providing ongoing support for blood cancer research THE WOODLANDS, Texas (PRWEB) February 09, 2018 Jared Moore, the managing owner of Houston area Moore Insurance Agency, is launching a charity drive to support research into potential cures and treatments for blood cancer. To this end, the firm has joined The Leukemia & Lymphoma Society (LLS) Man & Woman of the Year competition, and will be supporting local candidate Kalli Gonzalez on her mission to raise support for blood cancer research. “We’re excited about the upcoming Leukemia & Lymphoma Society event, and our agency is committed to providing ongoing support for blood cancer research,” said Moore. To improve community involvement, the firm will be asking residents to send in referrals to help generate donations. For each person referred into Moore Insurance to receive a complimentary insurance quote, the firm will make a monetary donation to blood cancer research. Additional details on how to get involved in the event are provided here: http://mooreinsuranceteam.com/rewards/ . About Moore Insurance As a Personal Insurance Representative in The Woodlands, agency owner Jared Moore knows many local families. His knowledge and understanding of the people in his community ensures that clients of Moore Insurance are provided with an outstanding level of service. Jared and his team look forward to helping families protect the things that are most important - family, home, car and more. Moore Insurance also offers clients a preparation strategy for achieving their financial goals. To contact an expert at Moore Insurance, visit http://mooreinsuranceteam.com/ or call (281) 367-8899. \nShare article on social media or email: \nView article via:",
