        "text": "Lower Cape Calendar: Arts, music, stage   CALENDAR Friday, Feb. 9 Labyrinth Meditative Walk The theme of the guided walk is “Light,” 10 a.m., Church of the Holy Spirit, 204 Monument Road, Orleans, free. For more information call 508-255-0433 or visit labyrinth@chsorleans.org. Fish Fry Orleans-Eastham Elks, 10 McKoy Road, Eastham, 5:30-7 p.m. For take-out orders call 508-240-5826. All profits go into the Charities’ Fund. Saturday, Feb. 10 Cape Cod Bird Club Walk Winter birding in Provincetown, 8 a.m. with Peter Crosson, free, all welcome. To sign up and for more information call 508-280-1678 or email pcrosson@emeraldphysicians.com. LEGO Club Build and play with the library’s collection, 11 a.m. to 12 noon, Brewster Ladies’ Library, 1822 Route 6A, Brewster. Art Demonstration Jenny Kelley, expressions of love and romance, 1 to 3 p.m., Tree’s Place Gallery, Route 6A, Orleans, free, all welcome. Library Music Program Out Late, Diana DiGioia, with guitarist J Hagenbuckle and vocalist Melody Masi, 1 p.m., Eastham Public Library, Samoset Road, Eastham, free. Harwich Conservation Trust Talk Science Coordinator, Mark Faherty, Climate Change and the Birds of Massachusetts, 2 p.m., Harwich Community Center, 100 Oak St., $5. Visit harwichconservationtrust.org for more information. Library Music Program North Side String Band, 2 to 3 p.m., Brooks Free Library, 739 Main St., Harwich. Wild Care Fundraiser Wild Winter Night, 5:30 to 8:30 p.m., Elks Lodge, 10 McKoy Road, Eastham. Food, live music, raffles, silent and live auction. $30 advance, $35 at the door. Reservations suggested: wildcarecapecod.org or email: events@wildcarecapecod.org. Sunday, Feb. 11 Public Forum Common Cause Mass., and Lower Cape Indivisible, Defending Fair Elections, 11 a.m. to 1 p.m., Brewster Ladies’ Library,1822 Route 6A, Brewster, free, all welcome. Talk Meadow Dibble Hilley presents, The Diseased Ship: Uncovering Cape Cod’s Connection to the Slave Trade, 12 to 1:30 p.m. at First Parish B