        "text": "Things to do in Door County, Feb. 10 to March 18 From Staff Reports, USA TODAY NETWORK-Wisconsin Published 12:20 p.m. CT Feb. 9, 2018 Calendar of events (Photo: Tevarak, Getty Images/iStockphoto) CONNECT COMMENT EMAIL MORE Send your organization’s events and activities to advocate@doorcountyadvocate.com or P.O. Box 130, Sturgeon Bay, WI 54235, preferably two weeks in advance but no later than noon Monday for the Wednesday edition or noon Thursday for the Saturday edition. Through Feb. 25 ROLF OLSEN EXHIBIT: “ELEMENTS,” through Feb. 25, Third Avenue Playhouse, 234 N. Third Ave., Sturgeon Bay. For hours, call 920-743-1760, thirdavenueplayhouse.com . Saturday, Feb. 10 DOOR COUNTY POND HOCKEY TOURNAMENT, 8:30 a.m. to 4 p.m. Feb. 10, Kangaroo Lake State Natural Area, Baileys Harbor. Take hockey back to the pond with a 4-on-4 hockey tournament. Six divisions: Open A (Pro, college, or junior level players), Open B (high school, organized, or recreational players), Open C, Classic (40 and over), Classic B, Legends (50 and over), Women’s Open A and Open B. Three-game guarantee. Beer and food tent on the ice. doorcountypondhockey.com/schedule/ . CANDLELIGHT PARTNER YOGA, 5:30 p.m. Feb. 10, Tree of Life Studio at The Spa at Sacred Grounds, 10453 Townline Road Ephraim. Yoga instructor Mae Daniels and her Valentine, Tony Speer, lead workshop for all levels of yogis. Reservations required, 920-854-4733. \"BROADWAY LOVE SONGS\" CONCERT, 7:30 p.m. Feb. 10, Birch Creek Music Performance Center, 3821 County E, Egg Harbor. Music by pianist Jodie DeSalvo and tenor Jonathan Zeng. Heavy appetizers, light desserts. $60. 920-868-3763, birchcreek.org/tickets . SNC DISTINGUISHED LECTURE SERIES: LOVE AND SACRIFICE: PRE-COLUMBIAN CERAMICS IN PERU, 10 a.m. Feb. 10, Door Community Auditorium, 3926 State 42, Fish Creek. Lecturer: Debbie Kupinsky, assistant professor of sculpture at St. Norbert College. Donation. LOVING SONGS WITH CYNTHIA STIEHL AND JEREMY KAHN, 7 p.m. Feb. 10, Door Community Auditorium, 3926 State 42, Fish Creek. $17.50. Purchase tickets at dcauditorium.org , or call 920-868-2728. Saturdays, Feb. 10, 17, 24 FEBRUARY FEST CONCERTS, 2 p.m. Feb. 10, 17 and 24, Shepherd of the Bay Lutheran Church, 11836 State 42, Ellison Bay. David Bell, Clarinet & Friends, Feb. 10. Bruce Briney & Dan Grantham, Trumpets, Feb.17. Paul Bellino, Brad Ward, Tenor/Alto Trombones, Charlie Schuchat, Tuba, Feb. 24. Tickets: $25 per concert, or $60 for subscription. $5 students, children. 920-854-4060, musicfestival.com . Sunday, Feb. 11 CLIMATE CHANGE COALITION OF DOOR COUNTY CHILI DUMP, 1 to 3 p.m. Feb. 11, Baileys Harbor Town Hall, 2392 County F. Contestants bring three gallons of chili. Patrons sample and vote for favorites. Patrons pay $10 at the door. Proceeds support public education and climate action programs of the Climate Change Coalition. To register to compete, email . VALENTINE'S BREAKFAST, 8:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. Feb. 11, St. Louis Social Hall-Dyckesville, N8726 County Line Road, Luxemburg. Pancakes and porkies, ham and eggs, cherry sauce. $7 adults, $3 ages 6-10, free age 5 and younger. UKULELE JAM AND SING-ALONG, 1 to 2:45 p.m. Feb. 11 and 25, Northern Door YMCA, Fish Creek. Open to all skill levels. No fee or membership required. . VALENTINE'S POLKA DANCE, 1-5 p.m. Feb. 11, St. Isidore the Farmer Church, 18424 Tisch Mills Road, Tisch Mills. Music by Mark Jirovec Band. 920-776-1555. Monday, Feb. 12 TOPS (Take Off Pounds Sensibly) No. 510, 5:15 to 5:45 p.m. weigh-in, meeting until 6:30 p.m. Mondays, Sturgeon Bay Moravian Church, 323 S. Fifth Ave. Use handicap entrance. Candy, 920-746-0555. JOB CLUB, 1 p.m. Mondays, We Are HOPE, 1300 Egg Harbor Road, Suite 124, Sturgeon Bay. Job seekers discuss new job opportunities, employment search techniques, challenges and share job leads. Employment Expectations. Hosted by the Door County Job Center. wearehopeinc.org/Events.aspx . COMMUNITY PLAYGROUP, 10:30 a.m. to noon Mondays, Sturgeon Bay Moravian Church, 323 S. Fifth Ave. Kathy, 920-559-0200. Feb. 12-13 \"GRAN TORINO\" (R) MOVIE, 1 to 3 p.m. Feb. 12, Sister Bay Library, 2323 Mill Road; and 1:30 to 3:30 Feb. 13 at Sturgeon Bay library, 107 S. Fourth Ave. Followed by discussion. Free. SHROVE TUESDAY PANCAKES, 6 p.m. Feb. 13, Hope United Church of Christ, 141 S. 12th Ave., Sturgeon Bay. Supper feast traditionally marking the final day of indulging before Lenten fasting. Music by Sturgeon Bay High School Jazz Band. Free. 920-559-9905 or www.hopechurchdc.org. Tuesday, Feb. 13 TOGETHER TUESDAYS, 9:30 to 10:30 a.m. Tuesdays, Sturgeon Bay Program Center, 1900 Michigan St.; and Northern Door Program Center Social Lounge, 3866 Gibraltar Road, Fish Creek. Light breakfast served; birthday celebration last Tuesday of each month (cake included). Members asked to bring a treat to share the first Tuesday of the month. 920-743-4049. NORTHERN DOOR COUNTY AL-ANON FAMILY MEETING, 6:30 p.m. Tuesdays. Call 920-868-3874 or 493-6300 for location and details. COMPUTER SKILLS CLUB, 10 a.m. Tuesdays, We Are HOPE, 1300 Egg Harbor Road, Suite 124, Sturgeon Bay. Hosted by the Door County Job Center. wearehopeinc.org/Events.aspx . UNDERSTANDING INCOME INEQUALITY WORKSHOP, 7 to 9 p.m. Feb. 13, Bertschinger Center, 7860 State 42, Egg Harbor. Explore income and wealth inequality, how it came to be, and how to lessen the income and wealth gap. $15, payable at the door. Sponsored by St. Luke’s Episcopal Church, Shepherd of the Bay Lutheran Church, Ephraim Moravian Church and the Unitarian Universalist Fellowship. Email Jim Black at . BLOOD DRIVE, 9 a.m. to 2 p.m. Feb. 13, Northern Door Community, 7845 Church St., Egg Harbor. Walk-ins welcome. For an appointment, call 920-825-7333 or visit redcross.org . DIABETES PREVENTION PROGRAM, 5:30 p.m. Feb. 13, Door County YMCA, 1900 Michigan St., Sturgeon Bay. Y membership not required. See if you qualify, call 920-743-4949, or email . DOOR COUNTY MASTER GARDENER PROGRAM: \"WHITEFISH DUNES-A BIOTIC BLUEPRINT,\" 7 p.m. Feb. 13, Crossroads at Big Creek, 2041 Michigan St., Sturgeon Bay. Naturalist and author Dale Goodner of Algoma explores the diversity at Whitefish Dunes. Free. dcmga.org. Wednesday, Feb. 14 TOPS (Take Off Pounds Sensibly) No. 1335, 3:30 p.m. weigh-ins, 4 p.m. meeting Wednesdays, Prince of Peace Church, Oasis room, 1756 Michigan St., Sturgeon Bay. Carolyn, 920-493-5081, or Arby, 920-743-6060. WISDOM WEDNESDAYS, 9:50 to 10:50 a.m., YMCA Program Center, 1900 Michigan St., Sturgeon Bay. 920-743-4949. WISDOM WEDNESDAYS , 10 to 11 a.m., Northern Door Program Center, 3866 Gibraltar Road, Fish Creek. 920-868-3660. YMCA COMMUNITY BREAKFAST, 8:30 a.m. Feb. 14, Stone Harbor Resort, 107 N. First Ave., Sturgeon Bay. Tasha Nicole Johnson discusses the Character Development Learning Institute, a YMCA program to test best practices for adults to positively influence character development of youth. Free. Register at 920-743-4949. WOMEN'S COFFEE CLUB, 8 a.m. Feb. 14, GLAS Coffeehouse, 67 E. Maple St, Sturgeon Bay. Edward Jones financial adviser Tara Pierre discusses financial market topics. To reserve a seat, call 920-746-0781. BEEKEEPING, 6 p.m. Feb. 14, Door County Cooperative Country Store, 317 Green Bay Road, Sturgeon Bay. Max Martin and Gretchen Schmelzer of Door County Beekeepers Club offer tutorial on backyard beekeeping. For details, email . BLOOD DRIVE, 11 a.m. to 5 p.m. Feb. 14, Sevastopol High School, 4550 State 57, Sturgeon Bay. Walk-ins welcome. For an appointment, call 920-825-7333 or visit redcross.org . MOVING YOUR WAY TO A HEALTHY HEART, 4 p.m. Feb. 14, Sturgeon Bay United Methodist Church, 836 Michigan St. Presenter: Callie Barber, Cardio Pulmonary Rehab at Door County Medical Center. Soup supper after the program. Free. 920-743-3241. Feb. 15, 20 SEVASTOPOL 4K REGISTRATION AND SCREENING, 7 a.m. to 7 p.m. registration Feb. 15; and 8 a.m. to 4 p.m. developmental screening Feb. 20, Sevastopol School, 4550 State 57, Sturgeon Bay. Families with children ages 3 to 21 not currently attending public school can schedule an appointment for screening to assess each child's development, hearing and vision. Sue Anschutz, 920-743-6282, Ext. 1132. Friday, Feb. 16 OVEREATERS ANONYMOUS, 8:30 a.m. Fridays, Ephraim Moravian Church, 9970 Moravia St. Joan, 920-854-4001. SOUTHERN DOOR STUDENT COUNCIL BLOOD DRIVE, 9 a.m. to 2 p.m. Feb. 16, Southern Door High School gym, 2073 County DK, Brussels. Donors must be at least 17 and weigh at least 110 pounds (age 16 with parental permission), and in good health. Walk-ins welcome. For an appointment, call 920-825-7333 or visit redcross.org . \"MOONLIGHT\" (R) SCREENING, 7 p.m. Feb. 16, Door Community Auditorium, 3926 State 42, Fish Creek. Donation. Feb. 16-18, 23-25 TAP PLAY READING FESTIVAL , 7:30 p.m. Fridays and Saturdays and 2 p.m. Sundays, Feb. 16 to 25, Third Avenue Playhouse, 239 N. Third Ave., Sturgeon Bay. \"Dead Man's Cell Phone,\" 7:30 p.m. Feb. 16. \"And A Nightingale Sang,\" 7:30 p.m. Feb. 17. \"Venus in Fur,\" 2 p.m. Feb. 18. \"How to Write a New Book for the Bible,\" 7:30 p.m. Feb. 23. \"The Dig,\" 7:30 p.m. Feb. 24. \"The Roommate,\" 2 p.m. Feb. 25. Stay for the discussion after the reading. Donation. 920-743-1760, thirdavenueplayhouse.com . Saturday, Feb. 17 CANDLELIGHT PARTNER YOGA, 5:30 p.m. Feb. 10, Tree of Life Studio at The Spa at Sacred Grounds, 10453 Townline Road Ephraim. Yoga instructor Mae Daniels and her Valentine, Tony Speer, lead workshop for all levels of yogis. Reservations required, 920-854-4733. LATINOS IN THE AMERICAN ELECTORATE, 10 a.m. Feb. 17, Door Community Auditorium, 3926 State 42, Fish Creek. St. Norbert College assistant professor of political science Saavedra Cisneros explores realities about Latinos in the United States, including growth and geographic trends, political facts and figures. Part of SNC Distinguished Lecture Series. Donation. BEN LARSEN IN CONCERT, 7 p.m. Feb. 17, Fireside Coffeehouse at Door Community Auditorium, 3926 State 42, Sturgeon Bay native. $17.50. 920-868-2728, dcauditorium.org . FIRE AND ICE FESTIVAL, 9 a.m. Feb. 17, Sturgeon Bay. Citywide snow carving. Blacksmith James Viste taps steel in Martin Park, Third Avenue and Oregon St., 10 a.m. to 3 p.m. Maps available at Sturgeon Bay Visitor Center, 36 S. Third Ave. Dinner, auction and gala, 6 p.m. Feb. 17, Stone Harbor Resort, 107 N. First Ave., Sturgeon Bay. ($75). 920-743-6246. DOOR PENINSULA ASTRONOMICAL SOCIETY: NIGHT SKY VIEWING, 7 p.m. Feb. 17, Leif Everson Observatory at the Stonecipher Astronomy Center, 2200 Utah St., Sturgeon Bay. View M81, Bode's Galaxy and the Ghost of Jupiter planetary nebula NGC3242. The event will be canceled if the sky is cloudy. EIRAWEN 20 CROSS-COUNTRY SKI RACE, 7:30 a.m. registration, 9 a.m. 10K race, 9:15 a.m. 10K race, Feb. 17, Snowkraft Nordic, 5736 Walker Road, just north of Sturgeon Bay. Skiers of all abilities welcome. Door County Silent Sports Alliance Trail Vision Initiative benefit. Sponsored by Pete's Garage of Green Bay. Registration and details, www.signmeup.com/122881. Bob Richards, 630-269-4872. Feb. 19 BLOOD DRIVE, 9:30 a.m. to 2:30 p.m. Feb. 19, NWTC, 229 N. 14th Ave., Sturgeon Bay. Walk-ins welcome. For an appointment, call 920-825-7333 or visit redcross.org . Tuesday, Feb. 20 MOVIES THAT MATTER: \"I AM NOT YOUR NEGRO,\" 4:30 p.m. Feb. 20, Unitarian Universalist Fellowship of Door County, 10341 State 42, Ephraim. Narration about race in America, using the writer’s original words, as read by actor Samuel L. Jackson. 920-854-7559. Thursday, Feb. 22 PENINSULA PRESCHOOL TRIVIA NIGHT, 5:30 p.m. doors open, 6 p.m. trivia Feb. 22, Alexander’s Restaurant, 3667 State 42, Fish Creek. Twenty-four teams of six compete in 10 rounds of questions. $30 per person includes food and beer. Proceeds benefit Peninsula Preschool in Ephraim. To enter, visit peninsulapreschool.weebly.com/news . Saturday, Feb. 24 MIDWINTER GATHERING, 4:30 to 7:30 p.m. Feb. 24, Landmark Resort, 4929 Landmark Drive, Egg Harbor. Door County Land Trust. $85 per person. 920-746-1359. Feb. 24, March 24 DOG TRAINING SEMINARS, 10 a.m. Feb. 24 and March 24, Door County Cooperative Country Store, 317 Green Bay Road, Sturgeon Bay. Seminars by Hope Blueberry, Hopeful Paws Dog Training. Free for friendly pets and their owners. Leash manners, Feb. 24. Trusting your dog off-leash, March 24. (312) 342-7721, or email . Wednesday, Feb. 28 HARMONIOUS WALL, GYPSY JAZZ BAND, 6 p.m. optional dinner, 8 p.m. concert Feb. 28, White Gull Inn, 4225 Main St., Fish Creek. $20. For tickets, dinner reservations, call (920) 868-3517. LWV CANDIDATE FORUM, 7 p.m. Feb. 28, Sevastopol Town Hall, Highway 57, next to Sevastopol School. Snow date: March 19. Three candidates running for two school board positions: Kimberly Denil, Jim Nellen, John Staveness. Submit questions for candidates to lwvdcprez@gmail.com. The forum will be videotaped and available for viewing at The forum will be videotaped and can be viewed on http://doorbell.net/video. 920-743-6842. Thursday, March 1 DOOR COUNTY PARENTS PLAYGROUP, 10 a.m. to noon Thursdays, Hope Church, 141 S. 12th Ave., Sturgeon Bay. All parents and caregivers of small children welcome. Parents chat while children play. Coffee provided. See Door County Parents Playgroup's Facebook page, facebook.com/groups/172397079832702/ . Julie Neuchter, 920-493-2577. Saturday, March 17 BLUEBIRD MONITORING PROGRAM, 10 a.m. to noon March 17, Cook-Fuller Center, 8166 State 57, Baileys Harbor. Presenter: Charlotte Lukes. Tools and materials for one bluebird box provided. (Additional kits, $5.) $10 Ridges Sanctuary members, $13 general public, $5 younger than 18. 920-839-2802. STURGEON BAY BREAKFAST ROTARY CLUB TRIVIA NIGHT, 6:30 p.m. registration, 7-10 p.m. March 17, JayCee Clubhouse, 340 Jaycee Court, Sturgeon Bay. Teams of eight people answer 100 questions in 10 categories. Prizes, appetizers. $15 per person. Paul Schmitt, 920-493-6635. Sunday, March 18 BLUEBIRD NESTING PROGRAM, 1:30 p.m. March 18, Newport State Park Nature Center, 475 County NP, Ellison Bay. Presenter: Charlotte Lukes. Free, but state park sticker required. CONNECT COMMENT EMAIL MORE Read or Share this story: http://gbpg.net/2nTOXeL From The USA TODAY NETWORK These sites are part of the USA TODAY NETWORK. Their content is produced independently from our newsrooms.",
