        "title": "Feb. 9 Community News",
        "text": "Search Loading... I saw an ad for a humane mouse trap. Reminds me of the wiles of the devil that women use to trap men into marriage. Men,... Feb. 9 Community News Christopher Koegel of Chocowinity sent in this photo of a Carolina chickadee surveying some grape jelly left out for orioles. Loading… \nToday \nLegion membership \nAmerican Legion Post 15, 200 American Legion Road, Washington, will serve as the center of an area membership revitalization and veterans outreach effort from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. The outreach will continue from 9 a.m. to noon on Saturday with an open house for veterans and their spouses, children, or grandchildren. Donuts and drinks will be available. For more information call Jim Zajc at 678-485-8228. \nCar seat check \nGreenville Fire-Rescue provides free car safety seat checks from 9:30 a.m. to 4:40 p.m. every Friday at Station 1, 500 S. Greene St. Trained experts will ensure child seats are installed correctly. No appointment is necessary. Visit the Greenville Fire-Rescue Facebook page for more information. \nNominations deadline \nThe Human Relations Council of Greenville is accepting nominations through today to recognize and honor persons and organizations/businesses at the city’s “47th Annual Award Ceremony and Reception” to be held at 5:30 p.m. on Feb. 24 at the Greenville Hilton, 207 S.W. Greenville Blvd. This year’s theme is “Celebrating and Honoring Those Who Make a Difference.” Nominees should provide services that strengthen communities and improve the lives of others. For more information, contact the Human Relations Office at 329-4494 or via email cdaniels@greenvillenc.gov. \nComing Up \nPancake fundraiser \nThe Beta Alpha Chapter of Delta Kappa Gamma International Society of Women Educators will sponsor a pancake breakfast from 7-9:30 a.m. on Saturday at Highway 55 restaurant, 1920 Smythewyck Drive, with pancakes, choice of bacon or sausage and drink. Tickets are $7 at the door. All proceeds go to grant-in-aid scholarships for ECU education major students. For more information, contact Cindy Watson at cindyjowatson@hotmail.com. \nHealth screening \nA free health screening will be held from 9 a.m. to noon on Saturday at Phillippi Missionary Baptist Church, 2665 W. Virginia St., Simpson. Participants will be screened for blood pressure, body mass index, cholesterol and blood sugar. Sponsored by Vidant and the Faith Health Partnership of Eastern North Carolina, sessions take 10-15 minutes and are confidential. For further information, call Valarie Gatlin at 916-6409. \nOpen house \nThe Winterville Historical and Arts Society will celebrate Black History Month with guest speaker Pitt County NAACP President Calvin Henderson at an open house from 3-5 p.m. on Sunday at the Winterville Museum in the Cox-Ange House, 2543 Church St., Winterville. Henderson’s presentation, “Contributions Blacks Have Made to the Town of Winterville,” will begin at 3:30 p.m. Admission is free, but donations are appreciated. \nAARP meeting \nThe local Greenville chapter of AARP will meet at 11:30 a.m. on Monday at the Pitt County Council on Aging, 4551 County Home Road. The guest speaker will be Kathy Sheppard, Emergency Services Coordinator for the Pitt County Health Department. She will speak about services offered by the health department. The meeting is free and open to the public. Contact Jack Hansel at 717-3611 or email jackhansel@outlook.com. \nNAMI meeting \nNAMI Pitt County will meet from 6:30-8:30 on Tuesday in Room 001 at Jarvis Memorial United Methodist Church, 510 S. Washington St. This month will be a “Caring and Sharing Time.” NAMI (National Alliance on Mental Illness) is a support group for family members and friends of individuals with mental illness and those living with a diagnosis. All meetings are open to the public. For more information call 902-NAMI (6264) or 355-6133. \nNewcomers Club \nThe Newcomers Club of Greenville will meet at 11:30 a.m. on Wednesday at the Holiday Inn, 203 Greenville Blvd. Lunch is $15 payable at the door. The program will be the annual silent auction. Reservations are requested and should be made on or before Sunday by e-mailing newcomersclubgnc@yahoo.com. \nVisit reflector.com/communitycalendar for a full listing of events.",
