        "text": "Don't start no shit won't be no shit The Five Most M OW HISS Moments In This Week’s House Intelligence Committee Hearing   This is Adam Schiff’s OH NO YOU DI’INT face probably. \nRemember when THE MEMO was released last Friday and immediately the whole entire US and A and several small island nations started LMAO-ing so hard they caused a LOL-quake that was felt in China? That was fun! \nOn Monday, the House Intelligence Committee (HPSCI) held a hearing to vote on releasing the Democratic response memo, the one that takes a big red pen to the Republican memo and shows which parts are bullshit (all of it), according to not only the Democrats, but also the FBI and the Department of Justice. They voted that yes, it should be released, for transparency! And they released the transcript of their hearing today, for super transparency! \nAnd now, the Democratic memo is sitting on the Resolute Desk, underneath all the other documents (Trump loves documents!) and Big Mac wrappers (Trump loves Big Macs!). Has Trump read it? Hahahahahaha, OK so the trouble, according to John Kelly, is that the Democratic memo is AS LONG AS TWO BIBLES (it is ten pages) and that’s too long for Trump to read. Anyway, Trump will get around to letting the Democratic memo out without redacting all the parts that make him look like a fucking idiot VERY SOON, you bet! (The deadline is today.) \nWe are not live-blogging you the whole transcript of Monday’s hearing, because girl it is Friday, so just no. But suffice it to say that oh man, the Democrats and Republicans on this committee hate each other, and oh man, we absolutely must take back the House in November, as in that is the bare minimum we must accomplish, because this is no way to run a country. \nHere are five of the most ME WWWW HISS moments in the hearing transcript, accompanied by moving cat pictures: \nIn this section, GOP idiot Peter King says UH HUH the DODGY DOSSIER has been disproven, because Trump asshole lawyer Michael Cohen says he wasn’t in Prague meeting with Russian agents when the DODGY DOSSIER said he was. In response Democratic Rep. Eric Swalwell is like “Cool story, bro. I fuckin’ DARE Y’ALL to subpoena his records, instead of just taking his word for it.” \nUH HUH! \nAnd here is GOP idiot Mike Turner of Ohio, who is not usually so mouthy, who is OBSESSED with how the Devin Nunes memo PROVED that Hillary Clinton and the DNC funded the work that led to the production of the DODGY DOSSIER. Of course, the Democrats and everybody else in the world are like, “Babydoll, everybody knows that. Stop saying it over and over again IN ALL CAPS WITH EXCLAMATION POINTS, because what you are saying is meaningless.” They make Republicans mighty stupid up there in Ohio. \nAnyway, Turner gets why the DUMBO-CRAPS are mad and want to subpoena Michael Cohen’s shit, because they must be real DEM-BARRASSED about how Hillary Clinton and the DNC funded Chris Steele’s investigation, which we just now learned many months ago: \nPerhaps Rep. Turner should go back to shutting the fuck up. \nADAM SCHIFF: Why are you fucking idiots talking about Michael Cohen anyway? \nGOP IDIOT PETER KING: Dossier! Dodgy dossier! \nSCHIFF: But your stupid memo was about how the FISA court somehow improperly approved multiple FISA warrants against Carter Page The Literal Actual Russian Intelligence Asset, because dossier information was included amongst MULTITUDES OF OTHER INTELLIGENCE in that FISA application. \nKING: Dossier! Dodgy dossier! \nSCHIFF: Jesus Christ. \nKING: Reclaiming my time! reclaiming my time! Adam Schiff just made me look like A Idiot! That means I get my time back! Reclaiming my time! \n\nMIKE TURNER: Can I interrupt Eric Swalwell a lot? \nSWALWELL: Yeah, once I’m done talking about ALL THE FUCKING TRUMP-RUSSIA CONSPIRACIES we have solid evidence of, and about how the Republicans flat-out lied in their dumb memo. \nTURNER: Can I interrupt Eric Swalwell a whole bunch more? \nSWALWELL: Eat me. \nTURNER: I can’t eat you unless you let me interrupt you, with my mouth. \nSWALWELL: I’m still talking, asshole. \nTURNER: Will you stop talking if I interrupt you again? \n(This is a long one, but get ready, because Swalwell is very good here.) \n\nMIKE TURNER: Can I interrupt Joaquin Castro too? \nJOAQUIN CASTRO: Pound sand, motherfucker! \nJesus Christ! \nBy the way, the question was whether Devin Nunes would FINALLY answer whether or not he wrote his dumb little memo with the White House, or if they wrote it for him, or told him what to say. At the very end, Nunes finally said, “there was no involvement in drafting the memo with the White House,” because we guess it took him a whole week to figure out how to answer that question with a technically true answer. \nBy the way, here is a picture of Mike Turner, who is your new favorite Republican idiot on the intel committee: \nWant a bonus MEOW HISS moment? OK fine, here is your boyfriend Adam Schiff, being extraordinarily CATTY to Devin Nunes: \nDAMN GIRL DAMN! \nOK it is your open thread now, you earned it. \nFollow Evan Hurst on Twitter RIGHT HERE. http://wonkette.com Evan Hurst is the Senior Editor of Wonkette. He spends his days deflecting the sad glances of his black lab, Lula, who would please like him to stop typing letters to the internet and throw the squeaky chicken in the backyard instead. Though the internet does not give him credit, it's probably his fault Aaron Schock is no longer a congressperson, due how Evan would not stay off his tail during the SCANDALS. (Not in a sex way, in a writing way!) Also, he writes songs and plays the piano, at the same time! Lastly, Evan is a Southern person, and thus is casting polite judgment on you, right now, for reading this. Bless your heart. \nThey certainly can’t do any worse than the Republicans. Blackest Noobs \nespecially in fucking Kansas, jesus what a shithole! BadKitty904 \nWhat’s left of it. Charles Insandiego \nI heard about this on Preet Bhahara’s Podcast, which is worth a listen-to. Lord Jim \nEthan Randleas, a high school senior and libertarian candidate for the office, wrote on his website’s “About Me” section, “I am running to shake up Topeka, breaking up the stranglehold of statism that has began to cast its dark shadow over our great state.” He added, “I may be young, but that does not mean that I am incapable of serving the people of Kansas.” \nstranglehold of statism that has began to cast its dark shadow over our great state \nlolwut? \nSomebody just finished their first reading of “Atlas Derp”. armed_bears \n== people who tell him he’s awesome. everstar \nA different relationship, like “plaintiff vs defendant”. Cousin Itt, hoi polloi \nOh, that’s just guy lockeruproom talk. (((fka_donnie_d))), SOB \nThe problem with Archie Bunker was that he humanized this bullshit. In hindsight, probably a bad idea BadKitty904 \nLet me just say that Republican Cat (that’s how I have that first gif filed in the monumental BadKitty Cat Archives) is the only Republican I love. clairence \nWhy must you separate America from the United States? Cousin Itt, hoi polloi \nGreat, now Dok is channeling Samuel Beckett⸮ Anna Rompage \nIf Trump relies on Faux & Fiends reports for his intelligence briefings and bases our national policies off of them, then why the hell isn’t the dodgy dossier taken more seriously by the majority… \nBut I digress \nLooks like brolly bunny’s multiplied. Of course, that’s what they do. Bill D. Burger \nOh my! 3rd in charge, Deputy AG Rachael Brand, announces she’s leaving the DOJ___after only 9 months on the job. \nHmmmm! \nuh oh. whoever takes the job will be the one to fire Mueller, right? Bill D. Burger \nEverything is up in the air at the moment. Crazee’ time in a Crazee’ FUBAR administration. CripesAmighty \nOnce Rosenstein is out of the way. UncleTravelingMatt \nI dunno. Quick check says she was part of W’s legal team during the recount, oversaw Alito’s appointment, and is absolutely dead into violating people’s civil rights for the sake of intelligence gathering. Oh, and she was a senior fellow at the Heritage Institute. “Clown Show” appears to be her milieu. CripesAmighty \nRuh-roh. Slo-Mo Saturday Night Massacre continues apace: Rachel Brand just bailed, leaving an opening for Dump to install a stooge who rises to the top of the toilet bowl when he flushes Sessions and Rosenstein. Shawn Charniga \nA position that high up will likely be subject to Senate confirmation. 51-49. Someone will flip. BadKitty904 \nI love when Evan lets his Southern show and calls people “Babydoll”… Crystalclear12 \n“Honey” is also acceptable if said with insincere pity. BadKitty904 \nAs someone who regularly addresses friends and strangers – much to my husband’s amusement – as “Sugar,”“Heart,”“Angel,” etc., I’m with Evan. Ms. MLG on Maui \nSame. It tickles people here on Maui. In the South, it’s common practice. BadKitty904 \nYou don’t even think about it. My husband was startled the first time my uncle – former Army Col. etc. – addressed him as “honey”… The Wanderer \nOT:. Rachel Brand is leaving the DOJ. I’m thinking that this is because Trump wants to fire Sessions and Rosenstein so he can ditch Mueller, and Brand left in order to stimey him. Lord Jim \nSwalwell and Schiff come from the Barack Obama school of verbal destruction – articulate, measured, but pointed. BadKitty904 \nI’m surprised the Repugs didn’t lodge an “Unfair Use of Braininess” protest. calliecallie \nhttps://youtu.be/AvBj0QNdjpU?t=69 UncleTravelingMatt \nI love pointing out to the Missus that even though she has been insured by the same company for nearly 20 years, and even though my existence has only been known to them since we bought a car a year ago, Farm Bureau still lists my name first in all correspondence. It drives her into an absolute rage. Joe Beese \nThe pleasure in deliberately irritating one’s significant other is one of the joys of domesticity. \nI can always annoy Mrs. Beese with a deadpan deli